      "num": 1,
      "text": "Which fundamental right guarantees that legal procedures will be fair and that individuals will be notified and have an opportunity to be heard?",
      "tag": "Due Process",
      "options": [
        "A. Right to presumption of innocence",
        "B. Right to due process in administrative proceedings",
        "C. Right to protection against self-incrimination",
        "D. Right to due process of law"
      ],
      "correct": 3,
      "justification_correct": "Due process of law is the constitutional guarantee of fair treatment by the judicial system, including adequate notice and fair hearing — applicable in both civil and criminal proceedings.",
